Java Streams API (All in One) -

Hello All, In continuation to the series of my interview questions, today Iâ€™m sharing stream related concepts that can help you ace your technical interviews.

ğŸ“ŒCreating Streams : Different ways

ğŸ’From Collections :

List<String> list = List.of("a", "b", "c");
Stream<String> stream = list.stream();

ğŸ’From Arrays :

String[] array = {"a", "b", "c"};
Stream<String> stream = Arrays.stream(array);

ğŸ’From Values :
Stream<String> stream = Stream.of("a", "b", "c");

ğŸ’Infinite Streams :

â€œStream<Integer> stream = Stream.iterate(0, n -> n + 2); // 0, 2, 4...
Stream<Double> randoms = Stream.generate(Math::random); // Random numbers

ğŸ“ŒCommon Stream Operations :
ğŸŒ´Intermediate Operations :

ğŸ”¹ï¸Filter: Select elements based on a condition.

List<Integer> list = List.of(1, 2, 3, 4);
List<Integer> even = list.stream()
 .filter(n -> n % 2 == 0)
 .collect(Collectors.toList())

ğŸ”¹ï¸Map : Transform elements.

List<String> names = List
 .of("John", "Jane");
List<Integer> lengths = names.stream()
 .map(String::length)
 .collect(Collectors.toList());

ğŸ”¹ï¸FlatMap : Flatten nested structures.

List<List<Integer>> nested = List.of(List.of(1, 2), List.of(3, 4));
List<Integer> flat = nested.stream()
 .flatMap(List::stream)
 .collect(Collectors.toList());

ğŸ”¹ï¸Sorted : Sort elements.

List<Integer> sorted = List.of(3, 1, 2).stream()
 .sorted()
 .collect(Collectors.toList());

ğŸ”¹ï¸Distinct :Remove duplicates.

List<Integer> distinct = List.of(1, 2, 2, 3).stream()
 .distinct()
 .collect(Collectors.toList());

ğŸ”¹ï¸Limit / Skip : Control the size of the stream.

Stream<Integer> limited = Stream.iterate(1, n -> n + 1).limit(5); // First 5
Stream<Integer> skipped = limited.skip(2); // Skip first 2 elements

ğŸ“ŒTerminal Operations :
ğŸ”¹ï¸ForEach :Perform an action on each element.

Stream.of("a", "b", "c").forEach(System.out::println);

ğŸ”¹ï¸Collect :Gather results into a collection.

List<String> list = Stream.of("a", "b", "c").collect(Collectors.toList());
Set<String> set = Stream.of("a", "b", "c").collect(Collectors.toSet());

ğŸ”¹ï¸Reduce :Combine elements into a single result.

int sum = Stream.of(1, 2, 3)
 .reduce(0, Integer::sum); // 6

ğŸ”¹ï¸FindFirst / FindAny :Retrieve an element.

Optional<Integer> first = Stream.of(1, 2, 3).findFirst();
Optional<Integer> any = Stream.of(1, 2, 3).findAny();